# UUID display

## Entity lists

Every table or list that renders domain entities must include a **UUID** column for the row's primary id (`id`, `userId`, etc.), typically as the first data column.

Use `CopyableUuid` from `@/components/data/copyable-uuid`.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — directory list
<TableHead>UUID</TableHead>
<TableCell>
  <CopyableUuid value={row.id} href={`/customers/${row.id}`} stopPropagation />
</TableCell>
```

## Copy icon

Wherever a UUID is shown (lists, detail headers, audit rows, foreign-key references), render it with `CopyableUuid` so a copy icon sits beside the value and writes the full UUID to the clipboard.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — truncated id, no copy
<span className="font-mono text-xs">{row.id.slice(0, 8)}…</span>

// ✅ GOOD
<CopyableUuid value={row.id} href={`/accounts/${row.id}`} />
```

## Props

- `truncate` (default `true`) — short label; full value on `title` and clipboard.
- `href` — optional detail-page link on the label.
- `stopPropagation` — use inside clickable table rows.

Do not add a separate copy control when `CopyableUuid` is already used.
